oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Architectural details
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: William Strickland's sketch of various architectural elements. Included are corbels, a Norman window, arches and details of columns.

William Strickland began his tour of Europe in 1838. In Rome, Strickland was fascinated with archtecture and antiquities. It was there that he drew the majority of his sketches. He remained in Rome until mid-April 1838.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:creator: Strickland, William, 1787-1854
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Crow-stepped gables; Columns; Windows; Architectural elements; Architectural decorations & ornaments
